            "content": "; Regression test for issue #731: --current does not apply with --end (BZ#731)\n; https://github.com/ledger/ledger/issues/731\n;\n; When --current is combined with --end <future-date>, the --current flag\n; should still restrict output to transactions on or before \"today\" (set via\n; --now).  Previously, --end overwrote the terminus used to resolve \"today\",\n; causing --current to be ignored.\n;\n; Using --now 2024/06/01 to make the test date-independent.\n\n2024/01/01 Past transaction\n    Expenses:Food    $10.00\n    Assets:Cash\n\n2024/07/01 Future transaction\n    Expenses:Food    $50.00\n    Assets:Cash\n\n; Without --end, --current correctly hides the July (future) transaction.\ntest reg --now 2024/06/01 --current\n24-Jan-01 Past transaction      Expenses:Food                $10.00       $10.00\n                                Assets:Cash                 $-10.00            0\nend test\n\n; With --current --end 2024/12/31, --current should still restrict to \"today\"\n; (2024/06/01), hiding the July transaction.\ntest reg --now 2024/06/01 --current --end 2024/12/31\n24-Jan-01 Past transaction      Expenses:Food                $10.00       $10.00\n                                Assets:Cash                 $-10.00            0\nend test\n\n; Verify --end alone (without --current) still shows everything up to --end.\ntest reg --end 2024/12/31\n24-Jan-01 Past transaction      Expenses:Food                $10.00       $10.00\n                                Assets:Cash                 $-10.00            0\n24-Jul-01 Future transaction    Expenses:Food                $50.00       $50.00\n                                Assets:Cash                 $-50.00            0\nend test\n",
